## What this commit does
Hardens client-side usage-summary computation in weave_client.finish_call. The
dict-output branch used to splat `original_output["usage"]` into the per-model
summary whenever the output dict had "usage" and "model" keys, assuming usage was
a mapping. Now it guards `isinstance(usage, dict) and isinstance(model, str)` —
exactly mirroring the sibling object-output branch a few lines below, which
already had this guard. The dict branch missing it was accidental asymmetry.

## Why (root cause)
Discovered while probing the litellm responses feature: a streaming Responses
call abandoned before its terminal `response.completed` event leaves the
accumulator holding an in_progress object whose usage is None. model_dump()
produces {model: ..., usage: None, output: []}. The old code did
`{**original_output["usage"]}` = `{**None}` -> TypeError: 'NoneType' object is
not a mapping. The error was caught (weave/trace/util.py logs "Error closing
iterator, call data may be incomplete") and NOT propagated to user code, BUT the
call was left in RUNNING status with no output/usage recorded — a corrupted,
incomplete trace.

