## Design decision (Codex consult, threadId 019ebd12-e158-7120-9c1b-fe23a4a3020e)
Option A (fix core, this commit) vs Option B (contain in litellm via a
responses-specific exclude_none post-processor like the openai integration).
Codex endorsed A as a narrow base PR: it's a genuine latent core bug affecting
ANY integration emitting partial/null usage in a dict output; the sibling branch
proves the intended invariant; blast radius is favorable (only stops fabricating
summaries from non-dict usage). Used Codex's cleaner form (extract usage/model
locally, single isinstance guard) rather than padding the elif condition.

## Behavior-preservation argument
Plain dicts were ONLY ever handled by this branch (the object branch uses
attribute access — `hasattr(dict, "usage")` is False). So routing all dicts here
and guarding internally is equivalent for the happy path (usage dict + model str
still enters) and strictly safer otherwise (usage=None / non-dict / non-str model
now skip instead of crash). Pydantic BaseModel is not a dict subclass, so no
overlap with the object branch.

